07/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling coalition partners on Monday (6 December) demanded changes to the government and the public administration ahead of the 2005 general elections. 
Social Democratic Party leader Skender Gjinushi said the changes are a tactical move to demonstrate the coalition's openness to reforms.
In other news Monday, Deputy Prime Minister Namik Dokle confirmed the government's commitment to respecting the rights and freedoms of minorities. 
Meeting with a Hungarian parliamentary delegation, Dokle said authorities intend to meet European standards in this area.
Also Monday, an estimated 3,000 Albanian university professors decided to continue their three-week strike for higher salaries. 
The professors are demanding a pay raise of 100 per cent and greater autonomy for colleges. 
(ATA, AFP - 06/12/04)
